comments.body:
@fecet thanks for the reporting this issue. 

i verified the behaviour and looked into the pasta init logic, `createPastaArgs()` indeed conditionally sets `--map-guest-addr 169.254.1.2` for out-of-the-box `host.containers.internal` support, but completely omits the `--map-host-loopback` counterpart, breaking the outbound packet flow from the bridge containers as you described.

because the pasta_linux.go file is maintained in the [containers/common](https://github.com/containers/common) repository and vendored into podman and the fix needs to be submitted there first.

@fecet please note https://github.com/containers/podman/blob/main/LLM_POLICY.md

The host loopback must not be reachable from within a container, this has nothing to do with inbound vs outbund differences. The --map-guest-addr option is mapped to the pasta ip which uses the default interface on the host as default.
So you will need to bind your services there not just on loopback. If you do want --map-host-loopback then you have to specify that user explicitly.
